From: Nicolas Michaut <nicolas@yumilab.com>
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: dts: sun8i-h3: enable 1368 MHz overclock OPP
Date: 2026-04-06

Re-enable the 1368 MHz OPP that Armbian megous patchset adds but
disables by default. Tested stable under full CPU load with adequate
cooling (heatsink + dual fan). Thermal throttle protects at 85C.

1368 MHz = 24 * 19 * 3 = PLL_CPUX (N=19, K=3) @ 1.40V

Signed-off-by: Nicolas Michaut <nicolas@yumilab.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h3.dtsi | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h3.dtsi b/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h3.dtsi
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h3.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h3.dtsi
@@ -101,7 +101,6 @@
 		opp-1368000000 {
 			opp-hz = /bits/ 64 <1368000000>;
 			opp-microvolt = <1400000 1400000 1400000>;
 			clock-latency-ns = <244144>; /* 8 32k periods */
-			status = "disabled";
 		};
 	};
 
--
2.43.0
